<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Completes First Satellite Ground Station </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2001150194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1446 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2001150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, January 20 (XINHUA) -- The first domestic 
satellite ground station built in Shanghai is now in operation. 
  It will open 1,190 lines in 11 directions to such big cities 
as Beijing, Shenyang, Harbin, Hohhot, Urumqi, Lhasa and Haikou. 
  This is the first of four such stations installed in China 
by 
the Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications. 
  The station, located in the city's southwestern suburbs on a 
site of more than 2.6 hectares, is a huge modern building with 
two cassegrain antennas, one being 16 meters in diameter and the 
other 13 meters in diameter. 
  The garden-like ground station, which cost 57 million yuan, 
can be linked, if so desired, to international telecom networks 
since it also passed the test of the International Telecom 
Organization. 

</TEXT>

